        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 9:28PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 927 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Southside in Independence County to near
Sylvania. Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch to penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hickory Flat...                   Charlotte...
Salado...                         Crosby...
Bradford...                       Desha...
Searcy...                         Heffington...
Cave City...                      Judsonia...
Locust Grove...                   Moorefield...
Huff...                           Worden...
Kensett...                        Pickens in White County...
Velvet Ridge...                   Roosevelt...
Plainview in White County...      Aetna...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for eastern,
central and north central Arkansas.</instruction>
